title: 10 Takeaways from Week 11
itunes:title: 10 Takeaways from Week 11
description:
DJ and Bucky discuss the Steelers surviving over the Jaguars (0:44), the Cowboys as the best team in the NFC East (2:59), Bears big win over the Vikings (5:50), Lamar Jackson adding a new dimension to the Ravens offense (8:25), Drew Brees looking better than ever (13:45), Colts are dark horse contenders (17:30), Von Miller’s still a game wrecker (19:30), why it’s too late for the Giants (23:00), Alex Smith’s leg inury (24:40), and Ron Rivera’s gamble backfiring on the Panthers (26:00).

Learn more about your ad-choices at https://www.iheartpodcastnetwork.com
